\v 13 Behold,\f + “Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an interjection.\f* I will crush you in your place,
\q2 as a cart crushes that is full of grain.
\q1
i#n#d#e#x#s#e#p#a#r#a#t#o#r
\v 13 behold,\f + “behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. it is often used as an interjection.\f* i will crush you in your place,
\q2 as a cart crushes that is full of grain.
\q1
i#n#d#e#x#s#e#p#a#r#a#t#o#r
Behold, I will crush you in your place, as a cart crushes that is full of grain.
“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an interjection.
